  "issue_title": "[Bug] Mirror merged-PR gate skips base-branch validation when default_branch is absent and repo has no additional_acceptable_branches",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nFor the mirror OSS path, `_should_skip_merged_mirror_pr` builds the acceptable base-branch set as:\n\n`acceptable = ([pr.default_branch] if pr.default_branch else []) + additional`\n\nThe base-ref check only runs when `acceptable` is non-empty. If the mirror payload has **no** `default_branch` (older/partial mirror rows are explicitly called out in comments elsewhere) **and** `RepositoryConfig.additional_acceptable_branches` is empty, then `acceptable` is empty and **the base_ref gate is skipped entirely**.\n\nAny merged PR then passes the base-branch rule regardless of `base_ref`, which breaks parity with the legacy path: legacy `should_skip_merged_pr` always has a usable default branch name because it falls back to `'main'` when GraphQL omits `defaultBranchRef`.\n\nSo miners can be scored for merges that would be rejected on the legacy path, or that should be rejected when mirror metadata is incomplete.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Configure a `RepositoryConfig` entry with **no** `additional_acceptable_branches` (or empty list).\n2. Use a mirror `MirrorPullRequest` where `default_branch` is `None` or missing in JSON (so `from_dict` leaves it falsy).\n3. Set `base_ref` to a branch that would **not** be allowed under normal rules (e.g. not `main`).\n4. Run `_should_skip_merged_mirror_pr` / load path so the PR is considered for `mirror_merged_prs`.\n5. Observe `should_skip` is `False` (PR accepted) even though the same PR would fail legacy\u2019s default-branch check.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nMirror path should match legacy semantics: there must always be a defined acceptable base set (e.g. fall back to `repo_config` default, mirror default, or at minimum `'main'` like legacy), and PRs merged to non-acceptable bases must be skipped.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nWhen `acceptable` is empty, the `if acceptable and not branch_matches_pattern(...)` branch does not run, so **no** base-branch validation is applied for that PR.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Python version: 3.12+\n- Commit/Version: current `test` (mirror scoring in `gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/mirror/scoring.py`)\n\n## Additional Context\n\nRelevant code (`gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/mirror/scoring.py`):\n\n- `acceptable = ([pr.default_branch] if pr.default_branch else []) + additional`\n- Base check: `if acceptable and not branch_matches_pattern(pr.base_ref or '', acceptable):`\n\nLegacy reference (`gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py`, `should_skip_merged_pr`): default branch resolves to `'main'` when `defaultBranchRef` is missing, so the acceptable set is rarely empty.",
